programme.title: PL Stories: Title Run In - True Turning Points
programme.desc: PL Stories takes a look at the forgotten moments that truly defined a Premier League season, offering new perspectives on the games that shaped title races. As the season nears its conclusion, two former Premier League players alongside two football experts revisit iconic yet often overlooked moments, such as Steven Gerrard’s infamous slip in 2014, which many believe ended Liverpool’s title charge. But could it have actually been the following match, when Liverpool let a three-goal lead slip against Crystal Palace, that sealed their fate? Our experts debate these key moments and challenge the common narratives that have shaped Premier League history, sparking fresh conversation on what really determined the outcome of those unforgettable seasons.(n)
